characters.name: Anole
characters.aliases: Vic
characters.deck: The reptilian mutant known as Anole was a student at the Xavier Institute. Openly gay and leader of the Alpha Squadron, he was recently promoted to the New X-Men squad before it was disbanded and is currently a member of the Young X-Men. He is currently enrolled at the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.name: Armor
characters.aliases:
Hisako Ichiki
X-Girl
characters.deck: Hisako Ichiki is a teenage mutant from Japan that studied at the Xavier Institute before becoming an X-Man. Her mutant power allows her to create psionic "armor", giving her enhanced strength and durability. She is currently enrolled at the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.name: Ariel
characters.deck: An alien from a glamourous planet, Ariel has the natural ability to teleport through doorways.  She gathered young mutants to form the Fallen Angels and later discovered that she was also a mutant, albeit one of her alien species.

characters.name: Archangel
characters.aliases:
Angel
Warren Worthington III
Dark Angel
Avenging Angel
The Fallen
Apocalypse
Death
Horseman of Death
characters.deck: A mutant and original member of the X-Men. Warren received his angelic wings at a tender age, as well as a unique healing factor in his blood. After being twisted into a weapon of Apocalypse, Warren became the cold Archangel.

characters.name: Banshee
characters.aliases:
Sean Cassidy
Madame Banshee
Irish
Death
characters.deck: Banshee is a mutant with a sonic scream. Born in Ireland, he pursued a career in Interpol, the X-Men, Generation X as Co-Headmaster, and founded X-Corp. He is the father of Theresa Cassidy as well as Black Tom Cassidy's cousin.

characters.name: Beast
characters.aliases:
Dr. Hank McCoy
Magilla Gorilla
Golden Armed Boy
Mutate #666
Beastmaster
Brute
Kreature
characters.deck: One of the founding X-Men, Dr. Hank McCoy is a mutant possessing animal-like strength and agility. Despite being covered in blue fur and resembling a ferocious beast he possesses an astounding intellect and superb wit. Beast is currently helping Wolverine run the Jean Grey School, while also serving as an Avenger.

characters.name: Beak
characters.aliases:
Blackwing
Barnell Bohusk
characters.deck: Beak's mutation manifested at puberty, developing into a humanoid/avian hybrid much like the physiology found in flightless birds.  He is amongst the number of mutants depowered due to the events of M-Day, his body reverting back to human form.

characters.name: Blink
characters.aliases: Clarice Ferguson
characters.deck: A purple-skinned mutant with the power to teleport.

characters.name: Cannonball
characters.aliases:
Sam Guthrie
Samuel Guthrie
Jet-Ass
characters.deck: Cannonball is a mutant with the ability to propel himself through the air like a human rocket. Over the years, Sam has grown from a New Mutant, to the leader of the original X-Force, to a full-fledged X-Man. He currently teaches at the Jean Grey School and is an Avenger.

characters.name: Bishop
characters.aliases:
Lucas Bishop
Luke Bishop
Arch-Bishop
characters.deck: Lucas Bishop is a mutant from the 22nd century that traveled into the past, becoming a temporary member of the X-Men. He has the power to channel kinetic energy, releasing it generally through beams of energy.

characters.name: Cable
characters.aliases:
Soldier X
Nathan Summers Dayspring
Askani'son
Nathan Winters
Chosen One
The Traveler
The Savior
characters.deck: Cable is the time-traveling son of Cyclops. He was infected with the deadly techno-organic virus at a young age, which he kept at bay using his advanced psionic powers. He also raised the mutant messiah, Hope Summers.

characters.name: Celeste Cuckoo
characters.aliases:
Three-in-One
Five-in-One
Stepford Cuckoos
characters.deck: Celeste is the youngest of the Stepford Cuckoos, a group of clones of Emma Frost created by the Weapon Plus program. She is currently enrolled at the New Charles Xavier School for Mutants.

characters.name: Cecilia Reyes
characters.aliases:
Reflex
Cecelia Reyes
characters.deck: Cecilia is a doctor and former X-men member. She is able to generate a force field that is tied to her life force. She had recently been spotted in Chinatown. Recently she moves to New York where she´s hanging out with Gambit.

characters.name: Chamber
characters.aliases:
Jonothon Starsmore
Decibel
Jono
characters.deck: Chamber is a mutant with psionic energy emitting from his chest. He lost his powers on M-Day, was kidnapped by a cult of Apocalypse and transformed into Decibel. Now he's a teacher at Jean Grey School for Higher Learning after regaining his original powers following the events of Age of X.

characters.name: Cloak
characters.aliases:
Ty
Demon of Darkness
Tyrone Johnson
characters.deck: Cloak is the personification of darkness itself. He is the Yin to his partner Dagger's Yang. A superhero of the streets, he wages a war against drugs and drug related crimes.

characters.name: Colossus
characters.aliases:
Piotr Nikolaievitch Rasputin
The Unstoppable Colossus
Peter Rasputin
The Juggernaut
The Proletarian
Petey
characters.deck: Piotr Rasputin is a Russian mutant who possesses the ability to transform his body into organic steel, giving him immense strength and durability. Colossus is among the physically strongest X-Men, and is a talented artist.

characters.name: Dagger
characters.aliases:
Tandy Bowen
Lady Light
characters.deck: Tandy Bowen is half of the vigilante duo known as Cloak & Dagger.  After a drug-related experiment awakened her powers, she became the personification of light, able to generate light and use it both offensively or defensively.

characters.name: Cypher
characters.aliases:
Doug Ramsey
Douglock
characters.deck: With the cerebral ability to understand all languages, Cypher was considered to be one of the weakest New Mutants. He was best friends with Warlock, but was killed while defending Wolfsbane in battle. He was forcibly resurrected during Necrosha, and soon returned to the X-Men as a powerful strategist.

characters.name: Darkstar (Petrovna)
characters.aliases:
Laynia Sergeievna Petrovna
Leynia Petrovna
characters.deck: The first Darkstar, Laynia Petrovna is a mutant capable of manipulating an immeasurable amount of darkforce energy. She lived and died in service to her mother country Russia, but was later resurrected in the body of the previous Darkstar, Reena Stancioff, when Reena was transformed into a Dire Wraith.

characters.name: Darwin
characters.aliases:
Armando Muñoz
Armando Edi Muñoz
Evolving Boy
characters.deck: Darwin is a mutant that evolves to survive anything, though it is involuntary. He left the X-Factor Investigations team after the battle with Hela in Las Vegas. He is trying to cope with his new acquired powers.

characters.name: Doctor Nemesis
characters.aliases:
Dr. James Bradley
Dr. Nemesis
Doctor Death
Dr. Death
characters.deck: Dr. James Bradley is a "self-evolved" mutant super-scientist, co-creator of the original Human Torch, and a former Nazi hunter. He is well-known for his acerbic wit, immense arrogance and love for all things scientific.

characters.name: Cyclops
characters.aliases:
The First X-Man
Fearless Leader
Slym Dayspring
Cyclops the First
Mutate #007
Eric the Red
Dark Phoenix
Apocalypse
Slim
Prelate Summers
Scott Summers
Basilisk
characters.deck: The first X-Man, Scott Summers possesses the mutant ability to emit powerful force blasts from his eyes. He is visually distinctive for the ruby quartz visor he wears to control his devastating power. A born leader, Cyclops succeeded his mentor Professor X to command the X-Men.

characters.name: E.V.A
characters.deck: An extension of Fantomex's nervous system. Following Fantomex's death, she evolved to take a humanoid form.

characters.name: Dazzler
characters.aliases:
Alison Blaire
Ali
The Disco Dazzler
Songbird
Dazz
Kimberly Schau
Ally
characters.deck: Alison Blaire is an Omega-Level mutant with the ability to transduce sound into light, which often forces her into reluctant super-heroism. She is also a very gifted singer and performer, hence her reservations in donning her uniform.

characters.name: Dust
characters.aliases:
Sooraya Qadir
Turaab
characters.deck: Dust was a student at the Xavier Institute and one of the New X-Men in training. She is identified by her Niqab, which she wears instead of the traditional X-Men uniform. She is currently enrolled at the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.name: Elixir
characters.aliases:
Josh Foley
Joshua Foley 
Golden Boy
Slick
Elixir
characters.deck: Elixir was one of the students at Xavier Institute and is known for his ability of biological manipulation which allows him to both restore life or take it on a whim, and is capable of incredible feats being one of the few active and confirmed Omega-level mutants.

characters.name: Emma Frost
characters.aliases:
Perfection
Black Queen
Ice Queen
White Queen
characters.deck: The former White Queen of the Hellfire Club, Emma Frost is a powerful mutant telepath who can transform herself into organic diamond. She has become an eminent member among the X-Men. A gifted teacher, Emma is renowned for her beauty, wit, and revealing attire.

characters.name: Firestar
characters.aliases:
Angelica Jones
Lady Comet
Angel
Angie
Miss Angelica Jinx
Firestar
characters.deck: Trained to be an assassin with her microwave manipulating mutant powers, Firestar grew to be a popular hero.  She spent years as a New Warrior and Avenger, retired during Marvel's Civil War, then joined the Young Allies. Recently she has become a teacher at the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.name: Fantomex
characters.aliases:
Jean-Phillipe
Uncle Cluster
Weapon XIII
Fantomex Prime
Le Pew
Apollyon the Destroyer
characters.deck: Fantomex is a highly evolved and technologically advanced mutate, developed by the Weapon Plus program. He is highly cunning, skilled in misdirection, and has a ship that is an extension of his nervous system named E.V.A.

characters.name: Frenzy
characters.aliases: Joanna Cargill
characters.deck: A former freelance mercenary that worked for Apocalypse, Frenzy joined Magneto as a member of the Acolytes and served as ambassador of Genosha. She recently joined the X-Men after the Age of X.

characters.name: Havok
characters.aliases:
Goblin Prince
Magistrate Summers
Alex Blanding
Commander Summers
Mutant X
Minister of War
Nexus of All-Realities
Protector of the Nexus of All-Realities
characters.deck: Havok is the son of Corsair and brother of Cyclops and Vulcan and has led both the Brotherhood of Mutants and X-Factor. After a stint as leader of the Starjammers, Havok returned to Earth and to his former team X-Factor. He currently leads Captain America's new Uncanny Avengers.

characters.name: Forge
characters.aliases:
Genesis
Maker
Skitch
Master of Machines
Iron Man
characters.deck: Forge is a Cheyenne with natural mystical abilities and the mutant power to innately comprehend technology and build anything he can think of. He's a former love of Storm and also a former X-Men and X-Factor member.After M-day he went insane and believed dead until found and cured by Cable.

characters.name: Gambit
characters.aliases:
Remy LeBeau
Remy Picard
The Ragin' Cajun
Robert Lord
Le Diable Blanc
Death
The Cajun Thief
characters.deck: Gambit is a charming master thief turned X-Man. He possesses the mutant ability to charge inanimate objects with kinetic energy, causing them to explode, he is also extremely agile because of his powers. Gambit's signature move is throwing charged playing cards.

characters.name: Hellion
characters.aliases: Julian Keller
characters.deck: Hellion is a powerful mutant telekinetic. He was a student at the Xavier Institute, leader of the Hellions squad and Emma Frost's prize pupil. Hellion lost his hands during Second Coming, received cybernetic replacements, and is currently enrolled at the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.name: Hepzibah
characters.aliases:
Lady Kitten
Mam'selle Hepzibah
Zee
characters.deck: Hepzibah is a Mephitisoid with a long standing hatred of the Shi'ar. She is the weapons officer of the Starjammers & love of Christopher Summers (aka Corsair). Following Corsair's death, she began a romantic relationship with Warpath (James Proudstar).

characters.name: Hope Summers
characters.aliases:
Baby Spalding
Hope Spalding
Messiah Child
Mutant Messiah
The Starchilde
White Phoenix
characters.deck: The first mutant born after M-Day, Hope Summers is believed to either be the mutant messiah or the harbinger of death for humanity. She is an Omega-level power mimic, and possesses a connection to the Phoenix Force.

characters.name: Husk
characters.aliases:
Paige Elisabeth Guthrie
Hayseed
Xorn
Paige Guthrie
characters.deck: Husk is a mutant with the ability to "husk" her skin to expose a new type and layer of skin underneath. Originally a member of Generation X, Paige graduated into the X-Men and is currently working at the Jean Grey Institute of Higher Learning as a Junior Faculty member.

characters.name: Iceman
characters.aliases:
Bobby Drake
Drake Roberts
Frosty
Iceface, the Living Popsicle
Mr. Friese
Rampage
Robert Louis Drake
Robert Parker
characters.deck: The youngest member of the original X-Men. Bobby is an Omega-level mutant, although it took some help from Emma Frost to realize this. Bobby's control of ice is vast; he can create shields, clones, spikes, slides and also freeze others. He currently teaches at the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.name: Jean Grey
characters.aliases:
Phoenix
Marvel Girl
Lady Jean Grey
Black Queen
White Phoenix
Apocalypse
Dark Phoenix
Karen Grant
characters.deck: Jean Grey was one of the five original X-Men. An Omega-level mutant telekinetic and telepath, Jean has gained near limitless powers as a recurrent host of the Phoenix Force. She is known for her many returns from death and as the deceased wife of Cyclops.

characters.name: Joseph
characters.aliases:
Magneto
Joey
characters.deck: Joseph was a younger clone of Magneto, created by Astra. He sacrificed himself to repair Earth's magnetosphere, which had been altered by Magneto. He has recently returned to cause trouble for the redemptive Magneto.

characters.name: Karasu
characters.deck: A mutant who gained her powers post-AvX along with her twin brother. She was taken in by Ogun when she was a baby. Legion rescues them.

characters.name: Jubilee
characters.aliases:
Wondra
Jubes
Vertigo
Abcissa
characters.deck: Jubilee, once a teenage mutant, became a member of the X-Men who could release colorful explosive plasmoids and detonate matter at a sub-atomic level. Robbed of her powers by M-Day, she has since been transformed into a vampire. Most recently, she rescued and adopted a baby boy from a meteor explosion.

characters.name: Karma
characters.aliases:
Xian Coy Manh
Shan
characters.deck: Karma is a mutant with the ability to mentally possess other beings. A founding member of the New Mutants, she is one of the few confirmed and openly lesbian characters.  She lost a leg and now has a cybernetic one in its place.

characters.name: Kymera
characters.deck: The daughter of Storm and Black Panther from a possible future

characters.name: Lady Mastermind
characters.aliases: Regan Wyngarde
characters.deck: Regan is the  daughter of the original Mastermind.  Originally an agent for the Hellfire Club, she joined the X-Men after being captured by Pandemic.  Shortly after, she betrayed the X-Men and joined the Marauders and eventually the Sisterhood of Mutants.

characters.name: Kitty Pryde
characters.aliases:
Shadowcat
Ariel
Sprite
Katya
Kätzchen
Kitten
Half-Pint
Pun'kin
characters.deck: Kitty Pryde, also known as Shadowcat, is a mutant gifted with the ability to become intangible and phase her body through solid material. A talented prodigy, she became the "poster child" of the X-Men. Kitty became co-headmistress of the Jean Grey School alongside Wolverine, and now mentors the time-displaced original X-Men.

characters.name: Lifeguard
characters.aliases: Heather Cameron
characters.deck: Heather Cameron is Human/Shi'ar mutant. She briefly served as a member of the X-Men, then took a leave of absence with Thunberbird, now, Lifeguard has returned to the Mutant Nation of Utopia as a member of the Street Team.

characters.name: Loa
characters.aliases: Alani Ryan
characters.deck: Loa is a mutant with the ability to dissolve the molecular bonds of anything she touches. She also gained the ability to breathe underwater from an Atlantean Amulet that her grandmother obtained from her friend who was Namor's old girlfriend. Unfortunately for Loa, she can no longer breathe normal air.

characters.name: Lockheed
characters.aliases: Lockheed the Dragon
characters.deck: Lockheed is a purple, winged, quadrupedal alien that resembles a small dragon. He is the longtime companion of Kitty Pryde with whom he shares a special bond. He is a valued member of the X-Men and founding member of The Pet Avengers.

characters.name: Longshot
characters.aliases:
Arthur Centino
The Lost Messiah
The Lucky One
characters.deck: Longshot is an extra dimensional rebel warrior created through genetic engineering. He has amazingly good luck, as well as superhuman agility. Formerly a member of the X-Men and of X-Factor Investigations, he is currently operating on his own.

characters.name: M
characters.aliases:
Monet St. Croix
Monet Yvette Clarisse Maria Therese St. Croix
Penance
Lady Penance
characters.deck: Monet St. Croix, also simply known as M, is a former member of Generation X and X-Factor Investigations.She is currently a member of Storm's all female X-Men team.
characters.real_name: Monet Yvette Clarisse Maria Therese St. Croix

characters.name: Madison Jeffries
characters.aliases:
Box
Gemini
characters.deck: Madison Jeffries is a mutant with the power to psionically restructure metal, plastic, and glass.

characters.name: Maggott
characters.aliases: Japheth
characters.deck: Maggott is an unusual mutant, with the power to digest anything through the use of two slugs that inhabit his body, as well as the power to gain strength from that energy. He was an X-Man and died at the hands of Weapon X.

characters.name: Magik
characters.aliases:
Illyana Nikolievna Rasputina
Illyana Rasputin
Darkchylde
Darkchild
Archimage
Red Flag #133
Lightchild
Enchantress
Sorceress Supreme
Shattershot
Black Magik 
White Devil
Snowflake
Master of Limbo
characters.deck: The younger sister of Colossus. Illyana Rasputin is a mutant teleporter, sorceress, and the former ruler of Limbo, who is currently a member of Cyclops' team of rebel mutants.

characters.name: Mermaid
characters.deck: She is a member of the flagship team of X-Men in her reality, Earth-9997 (Earth-X). Though she can fly through and breathe air, she is also able to breathe and swim through water. She is an ichthysanthrope (Were-Fish) or a fish/human hybrid.

characters.name: Marrow
characters.aliases:
Sarah Rushman
Lady Tibia
characters.deck: A mutant able to control her bone growth, providing her with armor, clubs, and knives. As a child, she was taken in by the Morlocks where she would form the terrorist group Gene Nation before joining the X-Men. Her allegiances have shifted frequently since then. She was de-powered after M-Day.

characters.name: Mindee Cuckoo
characters.aliases:
Irma Cuckoo
Three-in-One
Five-in-One
Stepford Cuckoos
characters.deck: Irma, also known as Mindee is one of the Stepford Cuckoos, clones of Emma Frost created by the Weapon Plus program. She is currently enrolled at the New Charles Xavier School for Mutants.

characters.name: Moonstar
characters.aliases:
Danielle Moonstar
Dani Moonstar
Psyche
Spellbinder
Mirage
Dark Rider
Chief
characters.deck: A Native American and member of the original New Mutants, Dani Moonstar was one of many mutants to lose their powers on M-Day. Moonstar currently uses her skills, experience and combat prowess to fight against evil as one of the Valkyrior.

characters.name: Morph
characters.aliases:
Kevin Sidney
Changeling
Crimson Pirate
Charles Xavier
Professor X
Proteus
characters.deck: Morph is a former X-Man and the shape-shifting funny-man of the Exiles.

characters.name: Northstar
characters.aliases:
Jean-Paul Beaubier 
Jean-Paul Martin
characters.deck: Northstar is the haughty mutant speedster affiliated with the X-men, though he was originally a member of Alpha Flight. He is most famous for being the first openly gay superhero.

characters.name: Nightcrawler
characters.aliases:
Kurt Szardos
Kurt Wagner
Gainsborough
Herr Indigo
Great Boggie
Fuzzy Elf
characters.deck: Kurt Wagner is a prominent member of the X-Men and former member and leader of Excalibur. He possessed the mutant ability of teleportation, as well as incredible agility and a prehensile tail. Nightcrawler was a devout Catholic, contrasting his demonic appearance. A swashbuckling trickster and former circus acrobat.

characters.name: Omega Sentinel
characters.aliases:
Karima Shapandar
Prime Sentinel
Malice
characters.deck: Karima Shapandar is a human Sentinel. Freed of her mutant extermination protocols, she struggles to maintain what little humanity she has remaining.

characters.name: Petra
characters.aliases: Christy Nord
characters.deck: Petra was a mutant with the power to manipulate earth.

characters.name: Omerta
characters.aliases:
Paulie Provenzano
Omerta
characters.deck: Paulie Provenzano was a member of the X-Men for a brief time known as Omerta. A mafia-wannabe, he was often joking around and flirting with the female team members and was also very homophobic and racist towards team-mate Northstar.

characters.name: Phoebe Cuckoo
characters.aliases:
Three-in-One
Five-in-One
Stepford Cuckoos
characters.deck: Phoebe is one of the Stepford Cuckoos, a group of clones of Emma Frost created by the Weapon Plus program. She is currently enrolled at the New Charles Xavier School for Mutants.

characters.name: Pixie
characters.aliases:
Megan Gwynn
Pix
Nightmare
characters.deck: Pixie is a fairy-winged mutant who can cause those exposed to her dust to experience hallucinations. Magik forged a fragment of her soul into a dagger which can disrupt magic and mystical beings. Pixie is a teleporter by means of a teleportation spell. She is a member of the X-men.

characters.name: Polaris
characters.aliases:
Lorna Dane
Polaris
Lorna
Malice
Mistress of Magnetism
Princess Lorna 
Pestilence
Magnetrix
M2
characters.deck: The mutant mistress of magnetism, Polaris is the daughter of Magneto and half sister to Quicksilver and the Scarlet Witch. After a long sojourn in space she's now rejoined the ranks of X-Factor.

characters.name: Prodigy
characters.aliases: David Alleyne
characters.deck: Prodigy is a naturally intelligent Mutant with the ability to mimic the knowledge, mental skills, and abilities of others around him. Prodigy lost his powers on M-Day, but regained his powers to some extent, and now has all the skills and abilities of everyone he met while his powers were active. He recently became a member of the Young Avengers.

characters.name: Professor X
characters.aliases:
Professor Charles Xavier
Prisoner M-13
The Good Shepard
Chuck Xavier
Consort-Royal
The Founder
Bald Phoenix
The Entity
characters.deck: Professor Charles Xavier is the creator of the X-Men and founder of the Xavier School for Gifted Youngsters. His dream of peaceful coexistence between mutants and humanity has long been the driving force for the X-Men. An immensely powerful telepath and scientific genius, Xavier was among the world's greatest masterminds.

characters.name: Psylocke
characters.aliases:
Captain Britain
Lady Mandarin
Butterfly
Lady Britain
Death
Betsy
characters.deck: Brit beauty Psylocke is a mutant with vast telepathic and telekinetic powers that she can focus into deadly weapons. She is a stealthy martial artist, a former fashion model and longtime X-Man. She is on Cable's current X-Force and is part of the all female X-Men team.

characters.name: Rachel Grey
characters.aliases:
Alyzr'n Summerset
Baby Phoenix
Bright Lady
Executioner
Marvel Girl
Mother Askani
Phoenix
Rachel Anne Richards
Rachel Grey-Summers
Rachel Summers
Red
Revenant
Starchild
Starchilde
White Warrior Princess
Ray
characters.deck: Rachel Grey-Summers is the daughter of Cyclops and Jean Grey from the alternate "Days of Future Past" timeline. She was forced to become a mutant "hound" and track other mutants before escaping to the present. Rachel has immense telekinetic and telepathic powers, and currently teaches at the Jean Grey School.

characters.name: Rogue
characters.aliases:
Ace
Anna Lebeau
Anna Raven
Anne Marie
Anne-Marie Rankin
Carol Danvers
Dr. Adler
Dr. Kellogg
Irene Adler
Legacy
Malicia

Marianne

Ms. Marvel
Mutate #9602
Reaper 
Legacy 
Thor
characters.deck: Once a member of the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants, Rogue has since become a veteran member of the X-Men. After many years, she has finally gained conscious control of her power to absorb the thoughts, abilities, and memories of others through physical contact. She is currently a member of both the Avengers Unity Squad and the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.name: Rockslide
characters.aliases:
Santo Vaccarro
Sanchez
characters.deck: Rockslide is a student at the Xavier Institute and a member of the Young X-Men. He is currently enrolled at the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.name: Revanche
characters.aliases:
Kwannon
Betsy Braddock
Elizabeth Braddock
Psylocke
characters.deck: Japanese assassin who infamously swapped bodies with the X-Man Psylocke. Briefly becoming an X-Man, Revanche contracted the Legacy Virus and died, although her legacy lives on in Psylocke.

characters.name: Shen Xorn
characters.aliases:
Shen-Yin
Zorn
characters.deck: Shen Xorn is the brother of Kuan-Yin Xorn and currently depowered following the Decimation.

characters.name: Sage
characters.aliases:
Lady Tessa
Britannia
Diana Fox
characters.deck: Sage is a mutant telepath with a computer-like mind capable of infinite recall. She has been a Hellfire Club Member, X-Man, member of Excalibur and Exiles.

characters.name: Slipstream
characters.aliases: Davis Cameron
characters.deck: Davis location has been revealed to be on Utopia along with his sister Heather Cameron.

characters.name: Siryn
characters.aliases:
Siryn
Sonique
Sy
Terry
Theresa Maeve Rourke Cassidy 
Theresa Cassidy
Theresa Rourke
Tracy Cassidy
Banshee
characters.deck: Theresa Cassidy is a mutant with sonic-based powers inherited from her father, Sean Cassidy a.k.a. Banshee. In honor and memory of her father, she took the name of Banshee.

characters.name: Shogo
characters.aliases: Sentinel X
characters.deck: An orphaned child adopted by Jubilee and briefly possessed by Arkea.

characters.name: Storm
characters.aliases:
Beautiful Windrider
Bloodstorm
Goddess of the Plains
High Priestess
La Reine Storm
Mistress of the Elements
Headmistress Ororo
Mutate #20
Orordius
Ororo Iqadi T'Challa
Ororo Komos Wakandas
Ororo Munroe
Queen Ororo
Weather Witch
White Queen
characters.deck: Ororo Munroe is a mutant with the power to manipulate the powerful forces and elements that pattern the weather. Taking the codename Storm she is a veteran member of the X-Men and the Headmistress of the Jean Grey School.

characters.name: Stacy X
characters.aliases:
Miranda Leevald
Stacy X
Mira
Ripcord
characters.deck: Originally a mutant working at a brothel in Nevada, Stacy X became a member of the X-Men using her Pheromone powers to help out her team. Depowered during M-Day she joined the New Warriors and recently she resurfaced with her powers returned in Vengeance.

characters.name: Spyke
characters.aliases:
Porcupine
Evan

characters.deck: Connor Hawke is the son of Oliver Queen.  During the time of Queen's temporary death, Connor took up the mantle of Green Arrow.  He is among the world's greatest martial artists and archers.

characters.name: Dale Gunn
characters.deck: Dale Gunn was on the staff of the Justice League Detroit Team. In the New 52 he is now a member of A.R.G.U.S.

The World's Greatest Acrobat
The Target
Robbie Malone
Renegade
The Boy Wonder
characters.deck: Raised in Haly’s Circus as a skilled trapeze artist, Dick Grayson studied under Batman for years as the first Robin until maturing into the hero called Nightwing. He would eventually assume his mentor’s role for a short term, but recently reclaimed the identity of Nightwing upon Bruce Wayne's return. He is currently stationed in Chicago. He also is the owner of Haly's Circus.

characters.name: Dr. Light (Hoshi)
characters.aliases:
Key-Chan
Kimi
Kimiyo
Kimiko Hoshi
Doctor Light
characters.deck: Dr. Kimiyo Hoshi, an astronomer, was granted abilities by the Monitor, during the events of Crisis on Infinite Earths, that allow her to control and adsorb a variation of different light energy. She's often been a member of the Justice League. She's the divorced mother of two children, Imako (her daughter) and Yasu (her son).

characters.name: Elongated Man
characters.aliases:
Ductile Detective
Elongated Man
Ralph Dibny
Randolph William Dibny
Strechable Sleuth
characters.deck: A long time member of the Justice League who recently lost his wife. Trying to make sense of his life post-loss, he sacrificed himself in battle. For a brief period of time he was a Black Lantern, but was destroyed by Indigo-1.

characters.name: Dinah Drake
characters.aliases:
Dinah Lance
Black Canary
characters.deck: Dinah Drake was the original Black Canary of the Golden Age, and mother of Dinah Laurel Lance, the modern (and more well-known) Black Canary.

characters.name: Element Woman
characters.aliases: Emily Sung
characters.deck: Introduced in the Flashpoint event, Emily Sung was among the heroes summoned by Cyborg to confront Aquaman and Wonder Woman. Element Woman is eager to help heroes however she can, though according to Shade, she's a bit mad. In the new 52, she is recruited into the Justice League.

characters.name: Faith
characters.aliases: The Fat Lady
characters.deck: Not much is known about Faith's past but she has helped out the JLA and Doom Patrol. The only person who knows about her past is Batman and he isn't telling.

The Blistering Babe from Brazil

characters.deck: Beatriz Bonilla da Costa had originally been bequeathed with her powers due to Brazilian mysticism. She was the President of Wayne Enterprises' Brazilian Branch. She has served as a member of various teams, but Fire is most well known for her team-ups with her best friend Ice.

characters.name: Firehawk
characters.aliases: Lorraine Reilly
characters.deck: Lorraine Reilly has a long history with the superhero Firestorm, both romantically and professionally.  She has the ability to create and control nuclear fire and fly.

characters.name: Firestorm (Rusch)
characters.deck: The "essence" of Firestorm found its way to a young man named Jason Rusch, and imbued him with powers very similar to the original.

Democracy's Only True Hope
General Glory

characters.deck: Joseph Jones was and American GI during WWII.  Granted  super powers by "Lady Liberty," Jones went on to become General Glory.

Prince Brion
Prince Brion Markov
Earth-Mover
characters.deck: Brion Markov is the king of Markovia. Thanks to breeding and science, he has the powers of the planet Earth, including gravity, earth control, lava blasts and super-strength. He's also co-leader of the Outsiders and a founding member.

characters.name: Guardian
characters.aliases:
James Jacob Harper
Jim Harper
Golden Guardian
Agent Harper
characters.deck: Created by Joe Simon and Jack Kirby, Guardian was once a cop named Jim Harper, patrolling Metropolis's Suicide Slum. Harper eventually becomes the vigilante known as Guardian to "guard" society from crooks.

characters.name: Green Arrow
characters.aliases:
Oliver "Ollie" Queen
The Emerald Archer
The Ace Archer
The Battling Bowman
The Dark Hunter
Auu Lanu Lau'ava
Robin Hood
Mayor Queen
The Hood
characters.deck: Oliver Queen was a spoiled, thrill-seeking playboy, until he was left stranded on a deserted island for several years. There, he trained to become a master archer in order to survive. After his return home, he used his skills to become the costumed vigilante called Green Arrow to dispense justice.

characters.name: Guy Gardner

Warrior
The Grinder 
GL
Green Lantern
The Crazy One
Green Lantern of Sector 2814.3
Red Lantern
The Gardner
characters.deck: Guy Gardner started out as the backup Green Lantern for Hal Jordan. He has since become one of the most prominent Green Lanterns of the Corps, despite possessing an egocentric personality. He has recently deserted his Green Power Ring in favor of the Red Ring of rage. Guy's will and rage are some of the most impressive in the entire Emotional Spectrum.

characters.name: Gypsy
characters.aliases:
Cindy
Cynnthia Mordeth
characters.deck: Cynthia Reynolds started her career as a superhero in Detroit with the Justice League of America. As the mysterious Gypsy she is an unseen defender of justice.  She has been associated with the Justice League Task Force, the Conglomerate, and the Birds of Prey.

characters.name: Hank Heywood
characters.aliases:
Steel
Hank Heywood III
Henry Heywood
characters.deck: Hank Heywood III was the second Steel and grandson of the original Commander Steel and cousin of Nathan Heywood AKA Citizen Steel.

Shiera Sanders

Shayera Thal
Sharon Parker
characters.deck: Hawkgirl is the reincarnated spirit of Chay-Ara. Born on Thanagar and was a lieutenant there and was sent to earth on a mission but she grew to love Earth and became known as the superhero Hawkgirl.

Shayera Thal

Shayera Hol
Shiera Hall
Hawkgirl
Ladyhawke
characters.deck: Pre-Crisis partner and wife of Katar Hol. At first, she operated under the moniker "Hawkgirl", but later changed it to "Hawkwoman".

Through shear will power and determination, Hal has established an impressive record of heroism across the galaxy with the help of his fellow Green Lanterns as well as his peers in the JLA.

Hawk
Khufu

Katar Hol

characters.deck: Carter Hall, now infused with the mysterious Nth Metal, is granted flight, strength and a living armor. He battles dangerous threats, both alien and mystical, as the savage Hawkman.

Hippolyte
Wonder Woman
Shim'Tar
Themyscira Queen
Hippolyta of Themyscira
Queen Hippolyta
characters.deck: Queen Hippolyta is the ruler of the Amazons and mother of Diana and adopted mother of Donna Troy. She is also the first and later the fourth Wonder Woman, after Diana and Artemis.

Helena Rosa Bertinelli
Huntress
Batgirl
Robin
characters.deck: Helena Bertinelli, born into one of Gotham's mafia families, became a violent vigilante destroying those that had killed her family. Though she has come more closely in line with other superheroes (after joining the Birds of Prey for instance) her methods are still harsher than most.

Sigrid Nansen
Icemaiden
Tora Olafsdotter
Tora Olfstotter
Ice
Sapphire
characters.deck: Ice-Maiden was the original Norwegian Global Guardian representative. She is a meta-human who can project ice and snow from her body, usually from her hands.  She also was a member of the Justice League of America.

characters.name: Jay Garrick
characters.aliases:
Flash
Golden Age Flash
Jason Peter Garrick
Jay Garrick
Man of Speed
characters.deck: Jason Peter "Jay" Garrick is the original Golden Age super-speedster and was the first to have the mantle of the Flash. It was Jay Garrick's legendary heroics that inspired Barry Allen.  Jay continues to inspire even today with his continued heroism as a stalwart member of the JSA.

characters.name: Ice
characters.aliases:
Tora Olafsdotter
Ice Maiden
characters.deck: Ice is a reserved and compassionate superhero who fights crime alongside her friend Fire. They've teamed up together as members of the Global Guardians and the Justice League.

characters.name: Icon
characters.aliases:
Augustus Freeman IV
Augustus Freeman
Arnus
Terminan
Black Superman
characters.deck: Icon is the superhero persona of Arnus aka Augustus Freeman, and member of the Terminan alien race. He crash-landed on Earth in the American South in 1839; Raised as a slave, but escaped through the Underground Railroad. After a series of events, he decided to become a Superhero and eventually joined the Justice League, after being drafted by Superman.

characters.name: John Stewart
characters.aliases:
John Stewart
Green Lantern
Green Lantern 2814.2
Darkstar
Hunger Dog
GL
Master Builder
characters.deck: Formerly an architect, social activist, and U.S. Marine sniper, John Stewart was selected by the Guardians of the Universe to be one of the Green Lanterns for Sector 2814. His distinguished service in the Corps has resulted in a place among the Oan Honor Guard and the position of chief trainer for new Lantern recruits.

characters.name: Jesse Chambers
characters.aliases:
Jesse Quick
Liberty Belle
Flash
characters.deck: Jesse Chambers is the daughter of the original Liberty Belle and Johnny Quick.  She previously operated under the name Liberty Belle as a member of the JSA. She also was a leader of The Titans as Jesse Quick, and is currently a member of the Justice League of America.

characters.name: Kent Nelson
characters.aliases:
Dr Fate
Golden Age Doctor Fate
Nabu
characters.deck: While in Mesopotamia with his father Sven Nelson, the famed archaeologist Kent unwittingly awoke Nabu from suspended animation. By releasing Nabu a poisonous gas was released, killing Kent's father but leaving him unharmed. Grateful Nabu mindwiped Kent and made him Doctor Fate, Sorcerer Supreme of Earth.

characters.name: Katana
characters.aliases:
Tatsu Yamashiro
Bladerunner
The Queen of Blades
characters.deck: A superb samurai, she uses her deadly sword, The Soultaker, to fight evil around the world. The mystic sword contains the soul of every person killed by it and Katana can communicate with those souls. She is currently a member of the Birds of Prey.

characters.name: Manitou Dawn
characters.deck: Powerful Magic User; inheriter of the mantle of Manitou Raven

characters.name: Major Disaster
characters.aliases:
Joe Smith
Paul Booker
Bennett Brodsky
characters.deck: A supervillain turned reluctant hero, Major Disaster is an Earth Elemental who is in constant indirect contact with "Mother Earth" herself, Gaea.

characters.name: Mark Antaeus
characters.deck: Mark Antaeus was a short-lived member of the Justice League of America.

characters.name: Manitou Raven
characters.deck: Powerful Magic User from the Obsidian Age of Atlantis

Green Lantern
Ion
Parallax
Torch Bearer
White Lantern
characters.deck: Originally thought to be chosen by chance, Ganthet chose Kyle Rayner because he had the ability to harness the powers of the emotional spectrum. Once the Torchbearer of the Green Lantern Corps, Kyle has since graduated to the role Ganthet had intended for him: the White Lantern.

characters.name: Metamorpho
characters.aliases:
Rex Mason
Element Man
characters.deck: Rex Mason was transformed into Metamorpho after he was exposed to the light of an ancient meteor while on an expedition to find the Orb of Ra for industrialist Simon Stagg.

characters.name: Matthew Tyler
characters.aliases:
Golden Age Hourman
Hourman 1,000,000
characters.deck: The third Hourman was an android created in the 853rd century by the time-traveling first Hourman, Rex Tyler. The android Hourman was an apprentice to Metron and a member of the JLA and JSA before sacrificing his life to save Rex Tyler.

characters.name: Mikaal Tomas
characters.aliases:
Blue Man
Cosmic Geek
Greg Bailey
Michael Thomas
Starman
characters.deck: The last of his alien warrior race and the third super-hero to use the name Starman.

Lady Maxima

Warrior Queen
Miss Superman
The Arrogant Aristocrat
characters.deck: The Empress of Almerac chose Superman as a mate, but became his enemy initially when her first advances were unsuccessful. While attempting to protect the Earth from the destructive beams of Brainiac 13's Warworld by using her warship as a shield, her ship exploded. Maxima has not been seen since.

characters.name: Moon Maiden
characters.aliases:
Laura Klein
Laurel
Laurel, the Moon Maiden
characters.deck: Laurel, the Moon Maiden, was a member of the original JLA but was erased from history, along with her foe The Centurian. Years later their existence reinstated itself on reality, and she rejoined the JLA to battle the Centruian once more...

characters.name: Mon-El

Lar Gand
M'Onel
Valor
Marvel Lad
Legionnaire Lemon
Jonathan Kent
Bob Cobb
Superman
The Man of Valor
The Wanderer
Superman's brother
characters.deck: Lar Gand was an explorer from the planet Daxam who sacrificed himself to save Earth. Lar, whom came to be known as Mon-El, was a member of the Justice League and friend of Superman in the modern era and is a member of the Legion of Superheroes in the future.

characters.name: Mr. Miracle
characters.aliases:
Mister Miracle
Mr. Miraculous
Scott Free
characters.deck: The son of Highfather, Scott Free was traded as an infant for Darkseid's child, Orion, to end the war between the New Gods of Apokolips and New Genesis. Scott later fled to Earth where he took on the mantle of Mister Miracle, and is considered the greatest escape artist in the universe. He is the husband of former Female Fury, Big Barda.

characters.name: Obsidian
characters.aliases: Todd Rice
characters.deck: Obisidian is the son of the Golden Age Green Lantern Alan Scott, Todd Rice is a shadow-controlling former villain, the twin brother of Jade, and one of the few gay superheroes of the DC Universe.

characters.name: Phantom Stranger
characters.aliases:
Judas Iscariot
Brotherless Walker
Grey One
Phantom Mouse
The Wandering Jew
The Stranger
Philip Stark
Wandering Stranger
characters.deck: One of the most enigmatic beings in the universe, the Phantom Stranger only appears when events of great magnitudes necessitate his direct involvement. Mysterious and all knowing, at one with the cosmos.

characters.name: Orion
characters.aliases:
Orion
Son of Darkseid
The Dog of War
characters.deck: The second son of Darkseid and scion of Highfather, Orion is New Genesis' greatest defender and the fiercest warrior of the Fourth World. Known as 'The Dog of War', Orion constantly struggles to maintain the balance between his peaceful upbringing and brutal nature.

characters.name: Mr. Terrific
characters.aliases:
Mister Terrific
Michael Holt
Pride
White King
characters.deck: Michael Holt aka Mr. Terrific is the 3rd smartest man alive. Mr. Terrific embodies his Golden Age predecessor's slogan of "Fair Play", and is currently the White King of Checkmate.

characters.deck: Former criminal Patrick "Eel" O'Brian became the super-elastic superhero known as Plastic Man. Often the joker of the group, he can stretch his body into any imaginable form.

John Smith
Reddy
Ulthoon
Tornado Tyrant of Rann
Tornado Champion
Tornado
characters.deck: An android created by the supervillian T.O. Morrow to infiltrate the Justice Society of America. Now it is a noble superhero and member of the Justice League.

characters.name: Retro
characters.deck: Today's hero, yesterday's attitude, Retro was a minor hero, the first one killed by Prometheus.

characters.name: Ray Palmer
characters.aliases:
Atom
The Mighty Mite
The Tiny Titan
Raymond Palmer
Shrink-Ray
Professor Palmer
characters.deck: Ray Palmer was the second to take up the name, Atom, and was one of many Silver Age reboots of golden age characters based more on science. Two others have taken the name after him but he has been the prominent of them in the DC Universe.

characters.name: Rocket
characters.aliases:
Raquel
Raq
Rocket Gal
Icon II
characters.deck: Icon's partner and friend, Rocket has a inertia belt that allows her to fly and form shields of kinetic energy. She's outspoken, liberal, and one of the first teenage mothers in comics.

characters.name: Roy Harper
characters.aliases:
Arsenal
Red Arrow
Speedy
characters.deck: Green Arrow's first sidekick, Roy Harper has grown to become one of the most accomplished marksmen in the DC Universe.  After being abandoned by his mentor, Roy, now going by the name Arsenal, joined the Outlaws with Red Hood and Starfire.

characters.name: Saint Walker
characters.aliases:
Blue Lantern
Saint Bro'Dee Walker
characters.deck: The first recruit to the Blue Lantern Corps, as well as its most recognizable. He was vital in freeing Hal Jordan from the influence of the Red Lantern ring, and one of the New Guardians after the Blackest Night.

characters.name: Ryan Kendall
characters.aliases:
Black Condor
Ryan Kendall
characters.deck: Ryan Kendall was the second Black Condor. A member of the JLA and Primal Force, Kendall was killed by Sinestro during the Infinite Crisis.

characters.name: Sargon the Sorcerer
characters.aliases: John Sargent
characters.deck: The magic of the Ruby of Life enabled Sargon to control whatever he touched. He also had some magical powers apart from the ruby.

characters.name: Shining Knight
characters.aliases:
Justin Arthur
Sir Justin
characters.deck: A Former knight of the Round Table in the times of King Arthur, Justin spent more than a thousand years in a frozen state. He joined the All-Star Squadron and fought alongside them for many years.

characters.name: Simon Baz
characters.aliases:
Green Lantern
Baz
characters.deck: Simon Baz is an officer of the Green Lantern Corp's Space Sector 2814 and a member of Steve Trevor’s Justice League of America. He received the fused power ring of Hal Jordan and Thaal Sinestro after their power rings presumed them both dead during the events of Rise of the Third Army.

characters.name: Starfire
characters.aliases:
Princess Koriand'r 
Kory Anders
Kory
Kori
Nova
Star
characters.deck: Formerly warrior Princess Koriand'r of the now-destroyed planet Tamaran, Starfire found a new home on Earth, and a new family in the Teen Titans. She has also served with the Outsiders, Justice League, R.E.B.E.L.S. and is currently associated with the Outlaws.

characters.name: Stargirl
characters.aliases:
Courtney Whitmore
Star-Spangled Kid
Starwoman
Star
characters.deck: Current bearer of the Starman legacy, teenager Courtney Whitmore serves as a valued member of the Justice League of America.

characters.name: Steel
characters.aliases:
John Henry Irons
The Man Of Steel
Hank Irons
Henry Johnson
Man of Mettle
Aaron Irons
characters.deck: Inspired by Superman, Steel mimicked his powers with technology. A genius of the highest order, he built a bullet proof suit of armor whose computerized pneumatic exoskeletal joints gave him superhuman strength. However, his greatest powers are his heart and determination.

characters.name: Steve Trevor
characters.aliases:
Howard Trevor
Steve Howard
Captain Wonder
Wonder Boy
Agent 47
characters.deck:
Colonel Steve Trevor is an Air Force pilot and the classic love interest of Wonder Woman.
He is now a U.S. Government Agent and head of A.R.G.U.S., an organization that serves as a link between super-humans and the government. He is also co-leader and a member of the Justice League of America.

characters.name: Super-Chief
characters.aliases:
Jon Standing Bear
Flying Stag
Saganowahna
characters.deck: Flying Stag is an Iroquois warrior who derives his powers from a talisman known as the Manitou Stone. His descendant, Jon Standing Bear took up the mantle of Super-Chief after him, but the stone was returned to Flying Stag after his successor's death.

characters.name: Tasmanian Devil
characters.aliases: Hugh Dawkins
characters.deck: A veteran member of the Justice League and the Global Guardians, Hugh Dawkins was born with therianthropic abilities.

characters.name: Tattooed Man (Richards)
characters.aliases:
Mark Richards
Sun-Chained-In-Ink 
Ink
Tattoo Armed Man
characters.deck: The 3rd super-villain to take on the mantle, Mark Richards powers are fueled by the sins of his victims. He is possess a pronounced hatred for the world's superheroes.

characters.name: Superman
characters.aliases:
Kal-El
Clark Kent
Clark Jerome Kent
Clark Joseph Kent
Gangbuster
Nightwing
Jordan Elliot
Superboy
Superman-Prime
The Action Ace
The Big Blue Boy Scout
The Last Son of Krypton
The Man of Might
The Man of Steel
The Man of Tomorrow
The Marvel
characters.deck: Rocketed to Earth as an infant from the doomed planet Krypton, Kal-El was adopted by the loving Kent family and raised in America's heartland as Clark Kent. Using his immense solar-fueled powers, he became Superman to defend mankind against all manner of threats while championing truth, justice and the American way!

characters.name: Tess Mercer
characters.aliases:
Tess Mercer
Mercy
Agent Mercer
Watchtower
characters.deck: Tess Mercer was born as Lutessa Lena Luthor and was the sister of Lex Luthor and the daughter of Lionel Luthor. She became a Checkmate agent and after Lex's disappearance, she took over LuthorCorp. Tess also became the second operator of the Watchtower and a member of the Justice League, but was murdered by her own brother. Months later, it was discovered that Tess's spirit is caught in Lex's mind and was freed by her friends later.

characters.name: Ted Kord
characters.aliases:
Blue Beetle
Blue Ishmael
The Big Blue Bug
Bumblebeeb
Deathmetal
Edward Kord

Theodore Stephen Kord
Theodore Steven Kord
Teddy Steven Kord
Ted Kord

George Bailey
George McCartney
Azure Avenger
characters.deck: Ted Kord was the second person to become the Blue Beetle. Deprived of the scarab that empowered his predeccesor, Ted was forced to rely on his superior athleticism, fighting prowess, and technological genius to combat crime. He died a hero fighting Maxwell Lord.

characters.name: The Olympian
characters.aliases:
Achilles
King of the Olympians
Warkiller
Achilles Warkiller
Wonder Man
characters.deck: Son of Zeus and incumbent king of Themyscira, The Olympian is a powerful warrior and a champion to his people.

characters.name: The Ray
characters.aliases:
Raymond C. Terrill
Night Boy
Ray Terril
characters.deck: Son of the original Ray, Raymond Terrill, is capable of turning his entire body into a living laser light.

characters.name: Tomorrow Woman
characters.aliases:
Tommie
TW
characters.deck: Tomorrow Woman was an android created by Professor Ivo and T.O. Morrow to infiltrate and ultimately kill the JLA.  She eventually went against her programming and saved the JLA by destroying herself.

characters.name: Toymaster
characters.aliases:
Toyman
Hiro Okamura
characters.deck: A teenage mechanical genius from Japan.  Unlike Winslow who uses old-fashioned toys, Hiro's inventions are inspired by anime and manga, including a giant Batman-Superman robot.

characters.name: Triumph
characters.aliases: William MacIntyre
characters.deck: Justice League's original leader, William MaccIntyre was lost in the timestream for years and forgotten by his allies. He returned after Zero Hour and struggled with his perceived loss of status.  After his return, he was a member of the Justice League Task Force for a time.

characters.name: Vibe
characters.aliases:
Vibe
Francisco Ramon
Cisco Ramon
Lord Vibe
Paco Ramone

characters.deck: The love of Bruce Banner's life, she has been one of the Hulk's greatest allies, though she is the daughter of his greatest enemy, General 'Thunderbolt' Ross. She has been transformed into the Harpy, died, and is now a Hulk herself. What's next in her life remains to be seen...

characters.name: Clea
characters.aliases:
Clea Strange
Sorceress Supreme
characters.deck: Clea is the heroic daughter of Umar and the niece of Dormammu. She is also Doctor Strange's estranged wife and was the ruler of The Dark Dimension until her Uncle usurped her throne and regained his.

characters.name: Cadaver
characters.aliases:
Cody Fleischer
Pale Horseman
characters.deck: Cody Fleisher was killed and resurrected as Cadaver. After the reaction of friends and family to his new appearance, Cadaver decided to remain with Dr. Druid and the Defenders.

characters.name: Black Cat

Party Hardy

characters.deck: Former cat burglar Felicia Hardy became a crime fighter when she became romantically attracted to and involved with Spider-Man. Felicia has the ability to instill "bad luck" around others - this comes in handy when fighting crime!

characters.name: Blazing Skull
characters.aliases:
Mark Anthony Todd
Flaming Skull
Smoking Head
characters.deck: A war-time hero, the Blazing Skull was an ally to the Invaders and remains active to this day although with far less sanity. In modern times he has fought alongside Thin Man's Invaders squad and the Defenders.

characters.name: Cloud
characters.aliases:
Carol Faber
Danny Milligan
characters.deck: Cloud is a nebula that took human form, and upon arriving on Earth was brainwashed by the Secret Empire. During a battle with the Secret Empire, the Defenders rescued Cloud and he/she joined the team.

characters.name: Colossus

The Proletarian
Petey
characters.deck: Piotr Rasputin is a Russian mutant who possesses the ability to transform his body into organic steel, giving him immense strength and durability. Colossus is among the physically strongest X-Men, and is a talented artist.

Captain Universe
Dr. Stephen Sanders

characters.deck: Dr. Stephen Strange was once a gifted but egotistical surgeon who sought out the Ancient One to heal his hands after they were wounded in a car accident. Instead, the Ancient One trained him to become Master of the Mystic Arts and the Sorcerer Supreme of Earth.

Dr. Druid

Master of the Unknown
Doctor Droom
characters.deck: Doctor Druid was a psychiatrist who was attracted to the mystic arts. After being trained by a Tibetan Lama, Druid gained mastery over some mystic arts.

characters.deck: As a child, Matt Murdock was blinded by radioactive waste while trying to save a stranger about to get hit by a truck carrying the dangerous material. In turn his other senses were heightened to superhuman sharpness and he gained a form of "radar sense". By day he is a successful trial lawyer but by night he guards Hell's Kitchen as Daredevil.

characters.name: Devil-Slayer
characters.aliases:
Eric Simon Payne
Agent of Death
Reaper of Souls
characters.deck: A former soldier whom came into possesion of a cape which made him Devil-Slayer, the demon hunter. Devil-Slayer served with the Defenders, and more recently, the Hawaiian Initiative team The Point Men and Wonder Man's anti-Avengers team.

characters.name: Gargoyle
characters.aliases: Isaac Christians
characters.deck: Trapped in the immortal body of a gargoyle, Issac Christians tries to redeem his previous evil acts as one of the Earth's defenders.

characters.deck: Trained by criminals and inspired by heroes, Clint Barton has grown from a troubled youth into one of the greatest heroes on Earth. The world knows him best as Hawkeye: Earth's Mightiest Marksman.

Henry Christopher Pym
characters.deck: Hank Pym is a genius, one of the founding members of the Avengers, the creator of Pym Particles and Ultron, a sufferer of Bipolar disorder and a modern-day superhero. He has acted under many memorable identities such as Ant-Man, Giant Man, Goliath, Yellowjacket, and the Wasp. He is also the Earth's Scientist Supreme, as decreed by Eternity.

characters.name: Hulk
characters.aliases:

characters.deck: After being bombarded with a massive dose of gamma radiation while saving a young man's life during the testing of an experimental bomb, Dr. Robert Bruce Banner was transformed into the Incredible Hulk: a green behemoth who is the living personification of rage and pure physical strength. He is currently an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D and operates as a member of the Avengers and Secret Avengers.

characters.name: Hellcat
characters.aliases:
Hellcat
Patsy Walker
Patricia Hellstrom
The Cat
characters.deck: Patsy Walker had long idolized super heroes and after given the chance of a lifetime became 'Hellcat'. She is one of Marvel's oldest characters, dating back to her 'romantic' comic books in the 1940s.

characters.deck: Cloned from the DNA of the Kree warrior Mar-Vell, a.k.a Captain Marvel, Genis-Vell was implanted with false memories making him believe he was instead Starfox's son and artificially aged to protect him from Mar-Vell's enemies. Unable to handle the mantle, power and awareness of Captain Marvel, Genis succumbed to madness as he became nearly omnipotent and sought to "fix" the Universe. Tragically, he was killed to save the universe by a self-preserving Baron Zemo.

He was transported to and became trapped on our world, where he became close friends with Beverly Switzler. Most people of Earth simply do not believe that he is a talking duck.

Bobby's control of ice is vast; he can create shields, clones, spikes, slides and also freeze others. He currently teaches at the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning.

characters.deck: Joaquin Pennysworth is the current Nighthawk and leads his own team of Defenders independent from the main team. A former SHIELD agent, Pennysworth took up the Nighthawk mantle when Kyle Richmond was forced to retire.

characters.name: Junta
characters.aliases: Manuel Diego Armand Vicente
characters.deck: Junta was a member of The Crew, an ally to Black Panther and War Machine and briefly a member of the Defenders.

characters.name: Interloper
characters.aliases: Will Fanshawe
characters.deck: One of the Eternals of Earth whom helped the Defenders defeat the spirit of the Dragon of the Moon that had taken over Defenders member Moon Dragon. He died, but was, with the other Defenders, ressurected by Doctor Strange

characters.name: Krang
characters.aliases:
Warlord Krang

characters.deck: Warlord Krang is a nobleman of Atlantis and a long time foe of Prince Namor the Sub-Mariner.

characters.name: Luke Cage
characters.aliases:
Carl Lucas
Hero for Hire
Power Man
characters.deck: Luke Cage, wrongly convicted and unjustly imprisoned, was altered in a failed prison experiment that granted him bulletproof skin and superhuman strength. With his street smarts, and unending determination to do right, he fights for the common man!

characters.name: Loa
characters.aliases: Alani Ryan
characters.deck: Loa is a mutant with the ability to dissolve the molecular bonds of anything she touches. She also gained the ability to breathe underwater from an Atlantean Amulet that her grandmother obtained from her friend who was Namor's old girlfriend. Unfortunately for Loa, she can no longer breathe normal air.

characters.deck: Hailing from Earth-8009, Lyra is the genetically engineered daughter of Thundra and the Hulk. She traveled to Earth-616 where she became an agent of A.R.M.O.R. and later joined the Defenders before enrolling at Avengers Academy.

characters.deck: Moondragon is a powerful telekinetic and telepath. She once possessed the Mind Gem, one of the Infinity Gems.  Although she is a cold, shrewd loner at heart, she was almost always a member of a superhero team.

characters.deck: Namor the Sub-Mariner is the ruler of undersea Atlantis.  The offspring of a sea captain and an Atlantean princess, he has been both a hero and a villain to the surface world. Namor is one of Marvel's oldest published characters with his origins in The Golden Age of Comics.

characters.name: Manslaughter
characters.deck: Manslaughter is a supervillain in the Marvel Comics universe. He is a psychopathic killer who has fought the Defenders, and later briefly joined their team.

characters.name: Nighthawk
characters.aliases:
Kyle Richmond
4-D Man
Blue Boy
Nighty
characters.deck: Kyle Richmond was a thrill-seeking playboy who became the costumed adventurer Nighthawk. Starting out as a villain, Richmond soon found altruism a greater pursuit. As Nighthawk, he became mainstay of the Defenders, and has also acted alongside the Squadron Supreme, the Redeemers, the Thunderbolts and the Initiative.

From that point on Jennifer Walters was able to transform into the Sensational She-Hulk; a recurring member of the Avengers.

Ben was an ace test-pilot until exposure to intense cosmic radiation mutated him into a rock-skinned monster with immense superhuman strength.  Ben's exterior is as hard as stone and he has a gruff disposition, but inside he has a heart of gold.
